scheduled_maintenances.name: Announcing IP Address Changes (No Operational Impact)

incident_updates.body:
The table for Zoom Phone rules has been updated to include the use of the UDP protocols for TURN (Traversal Using Relays around NAT) support (UDP 3478). Due to this, we recommend that network administrators, with Zoom-specific firewall or network rules, update their systems. This update is only for the protocol; no changes have been made to the destination addresses used for Zoom Phone. Below are the IP ranges that will be utilized for TURN support (UDP 3478).

Zoom Phone IPv4 ranges for TURN support:

144.195.0.0/16
147.124.96.0/19
170.114.0.0/16
173.231.92.0/24
206.247.0.0/16

As a reminder, these ranges were previously announced and are already in use for Zoom Phone. 

For a complete list, please see: 
https://assets.zoom.us/docs/ipranges/ZoomPhone.txt
 
A complete list of network firewall IP ranges for Zoom can be found on the Zoom Support site at: https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0060548

scheduled_maintenances.name: Scheduled Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Update (2/7/2026)

incident_updates.body:
Zoom will be enforcing a new minimum version for the following areas, approximately 90 days from now on February 7, 2026:

- VDI client
- Zoom Node (including Meeting Connector ZC, MMR, and Conference Room Connector Hybrid)

Additionally, beginning with the February 2026 enforcement, Zoom will require a minimum version for Cobrowse SDK. 

All other clients and plugins not listed here will maintain the same version requirements as the November 2025 enforcement. 

For more information, such as specific versions we are enforcing, refer to the Zoom Software Quarterly Lifecycle Policy support article: https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0061130 

To assist with checking the client versions on your account, refer to the Dashboard support article: https://support.zoom.com/hc/en/article?id=zm_kb&sysparm_article=KB0062208#h_13ce9a73-91e5-4df6-9cb5-c815b1605cf5

scheduled_maintenances.name: India Data Centers CRC Capacity Expansion

incident_updates.body: Scheduled maintenance is currently in progress. We will provide updates as necessary.

Zoom is continuously optimizing our global footprint to improve performance and availability for our customers. With this in mind, Zoom plans to decommission our Conference Room Connector (CRC) services in our India legacy data centers and move services to our newer India data centers. The locations we are moving out of and their replacements, are listed in the tables below.

Zoom customers using Conference Room Connector (CRC) to connect to Zoom meetings using  Zoom CRC DNS domain names for India region migrate to new DNS in2.zoomcrc.com

Zoom customers using Conference Room Connector (CRC) to connect to Zoom meetings using the CRC IP addresses for the old data centers must begin using the new CRC IP addresses listed in the table before the decommissioning date of February 27, 2026. 

Please be advised that Zoom meeting invites sent before February 7, 2026 may list the old CRC IP addresses. 


India Region

Old data center HY CRC IP address:  115.114.115.7 

New data center HY2 CRC IP address : 137.66.140.8

Old data center MB CRC IP address: 115.114.131.7

New data center MB2 CRC IP address: 137.66.136.22
